Single-cell ATAC-seq and multiome analyses

2024-10-17

Refer to Signac Vignettes Analyzing PBMC scATAC-seq: https://stuartlab.org/signac/articles/pbmc_vignette Joint RNA and ATAC analysis: https://stuartlab.org/signac/articles/pbmc_multiomic Motif analysis with Signac: https://stuartlab.org/signac/articles/motif_vignette

Specify File Paths

counts_dir <- "/maps/projects/ralab/data/projects/sc_course/input_data/filtered_feature_bc_matrix/"

metadata_path <- "/maps/projects/ralab/data/projects/sc_course/input_data/10k_PBMC_Multiome_nextgem_Chromium_X_per_barcode_metrics.csv"

seurat_obj_rna <- "/maps/projects/ralab/data/projects/sc_course/output_data/20241015_pbmc_RNA_qc_annotated.rds" # replace it with Robert's scRNA final seurat result

seurat_obj_output <- "/maps/projects/ralab/data/projects/sc_course/output_data/pbmc.ATAC.rds"

Data Loading

counts <- Read10X(counts_dir)
metadata <- read.csv(
  file = metadata_path,
  header = TRUE,
  row.names = 1
)
pbmc_rna <- readRDS(seurat_obj_rna)
pbmc_rna <- UpdateSeuratObject(pbmc_rna)

Create Chromatin Assay

chrom_assay <- CreateChromatinAssay(
  counts = counts$Peaks,
  sep = c(":", "-"),
  fragments = frag_path,
  min.cells = 10,
  min.features = 200
)
## Computing hash
pbmc_atac <- CreateSeuratObject(
  counts = chrom_assay,
  assay = "peaks",
  meta.data = metadata
)

Filter Chromosomes

peaks.keep <- seqnames(granges(pbmc_atac)) %in% standardChromosomes(granges(pbmc_atac))
pbmc_atac <- pbmc_atac[as.vector(peaks.keep), ]

# Compute nucleosome signal score, TSS enrichment score, and fractions

## Computing TSS enrichment score
pbmc_atac$pct_reads_in_peaks <- pbmc_atac$atac_peak_region_fragments / pbmc_atac$atac_fragments * 100
pbmc_atac$blacklist_ratio <- FractionCountsInRegion(
  object = pbmc_atac, 
  assay = 'peaks',
  regions = blacklist_hg38_unified
)

DensityScatter(pbmc_atac, x = 'nCount_peaks', y = 'TSS.enrichment', log_x = TRUE, quantiles = TRUE)

pbmc_atac$nucleosome_group <- ifelse(pbmc_atac$nucleosome_signal > 2, 'NS > 2', 'NS < 2')
FragmentHistogram(object = pbmc_atac, group.by = 'nucleosome_group')

Subsetting, UMAP, and Clustering

# Subset data
pbmc_atac <- subset(
  x = pbmc_atac,
  subset = nCount_peaks > 10000 &
    nCount_peaks < 100000 &
    pct_reads_in_peaks > 40 &
    blacklist_ratio < 0.01 &
    nucleosome_signal < 2 &
    TSS.enrichment > 4
)

# Dimensionality reduction and clustering
pbmc_atac <- RunTFIDF(pbmc_atac)
## Performing TF-IDF normalization
pbmc_atac <- FindTopFeatures(pbmc_atac, min.cutoff = 'q0')
pbmc_atac <- RunSVD(pbmc_atac)
## Running SVD
## Scaling cell embeddings
DepthCor(pbmc_atac)

pbmc_atac <- RunUMAP(object = pbmc_atac, reduction = 'lsi', dims = 2:30)

Gene Activity and Feature Plotting

gene.activities <- GeneActivity(pbmc_atac)
## Extracting gene coordinates
## Extracting reads overlapping genomic regions
# Add the gene activity matrix to the Seurat object as a new assay and normalize it

  object = pbmc_atac,

  normalization.method = 'LogNormalize',
  scale.factor = median(pbmc_atac$nCount_RNA)

Identify Major Predicted IDs

predicted_id_counts <- table(pbmc_atac$predicted.id)
major_predicted_ids <- names(predicted_id_counts[predicted_id_counts > 20])
pbmc_atac <- pbmc_atac[, pbmc_atac$predicted.id %in% major_predicted_ids]
Idents(pbmc_atac) <- pbmc_atac$predicted.id

Differential Accessibility Analysis

DefaultAssay(pbmc_atac) <- 'peaks'
da_peaks <- FindMarkers(
  object = pbmc_atac,
  ident.1 = "CD4 Naive",
  ident.2 = "CD14+ Monocytes",
  test.use = 'wilcox',
  min.pct = 0.1
)

Find Differential Activity of Motifs between Cell Types

differential.activity <- FindMarkers(
  object = pbmc_atac,
  ident.1 = "CD4 Naive",
  ident.2 = "CD14+ Monocytes",
  only.pos = TRUE,
  mean.fxn = rowMeans,
  fc.name = "avg_diff"
)

Plot Differential Activity for Top Motifs
